{"id": "EUVD-2023-59718", "enisaUuid": "722975cc-7d75-3f1f-92c5-7ae8c66644a9", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\ndrm/i915: Fix a memory leak with reused mmap_offset\n\ndrm_vma_node_allow() and drm_vma_node_revoke() should be called in\nbalanced pairs. We call drm_vma_node_allow() once per-file everytime a\nuser calls mmap_offset, but only call drm_vma_node_revoke once per-file\non each mmap_offset. As the mmap_offset is reused by the client, the\nper-file vm_count may remain non-zero and the rbtree leaked.\n\nCall drm_vma_node_allow_once() instead to prevent that memory leak.", "datePublished": "2025-03-27T16:43:34", "dateUpdated": "2025-10-01T20:17:03", "baseScore": 5.5, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H", "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/0bdc4b4ba7206c452ee81c82fa66e39d0e1780fb", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/0220e4fe178c3390eb0291cdb34912d66972db8a"], "aliases": ["CVE-2023-53002"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "45f64bdd-808b-3dcf-85ce-652f892de412", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "7865559872074a9ab169c87915504661d630addf <0bdc4b4ba7206c452ee81c82fa66e39d0e1780fb"}, {"id": "5c1debd9-0cc8-3583-b6cd-f9ef9870b8bf", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "61d6c560-396e-3c92-9be6-e183777fc4d8", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "7865559872074a9ab169c87915504661d630addf <0220e4fe178c3390eb0291cdb34912d66972db8a"}, {"id": "928cf989-cc22-35ed-ad31-fed112812061", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.1.9"}, {"id": "b5115fb1-c1f6-3664-8564-cc51a43b62d8", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.2"}, {"id": "d3c5ea01-6835-32c6-a1fe-2bbfc55ba15d", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5.7"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "0df322b7-9de6-3f8c-b965-ef19867d6e0a", "vendor": {"name": "Linux"}}], "isExploited": fals